WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.000
Moshe Sharett appears, a sudden presence
in the

00:03.000 --> 00:03.210
room.

00:03.210 --> 00:04.260
Did anyone notice his arrival?

00:04.260 --> 00:04.680
With great

00:04.680 --> 00:09.240
responsibility comes the weight of
history, a burden

00:09.240 --> 00:10.170
often unseen.

00:10.170 --> 00:12.960
Strange's hands move deftly, shaping
international

00:12.960 --> 00:13.677
treaties.

00:13.677 --> 00:18.696
Ben-Gurion's imposing shadow looms large
on the

00:18.696 --> 00:19.944
screen, a constant reminder of his
enduring power.

00:19.944 --> 00:20.952
He remains in office.

00:20.952 --> 00:21.960
Is it 1955 already?

00:21.960 --> 00:23.868
The air crackles with unspoken tensions.

00:23.868 --> 00:24.504
Who is

00:24.504 --> 00:25.356
the Prime Minister now?

00:25.356 --> 00:26.208
The question hangs heavy,

00:26.208 --> 00:26.490
unanswered.

00:26.490 --> 00:28.464
A sense of uncertainty pervades the room,

00:28.464 --> 00:29.724
thick and suffocating.

00:29.724 --> 00:31.824
The weight of decisions rests

00:31.824 --> 00:33.048
heavily on their shoulders.

00:33.048 --> 00:34.272
The future of the

00:34.272 --> 00:35.802
nation hangs in the balance.

00:35.802 --> 00:36.720
Each move is

00:36.720 --> 00:37.332
fraught with consequence.

00:37.332 --> 00:38.352
The clock ticks relentlessly, marking

00:38.352 --> 00:42.984
the passage of time and the urgency of

00:42.984 --> 00:44.052
the moment.

00:44.052 --> 00:47.256
A silent prayer escapes Sharett's lips,

00:47.256 --> 00:49.002
a plea for wisdom and strength.

00:49.002 --> 00:49.584
The fate

00:49.584 --> 00:51.528
of many rests on the decisions made
tonight.

00:51.528 --> 00:53.565
The weight of the world presses down.

00:53.565 --> 00:53.856
History

00:53.856 --> 00:54.684
watches, silent and judging.

00:54.684 --> 00:55.512
The future remains uncertain.

